menu "C library"

choice
    prompt "C library"
    default LIBC_PICOLIBC
    help
      Which C library the firmware links against.

config LIBC_NEWLIB
    bool "Newlib (full)"
    help
      Full newlib from the toolchain. Largest, but complete C99
      formatted I/O out of the box.

config LIBC_NEWLIB_NANO
    bool "Newlib nano"
    help
      Size-optimized newlib (nano.specs). Smaller than full newlib,
      but its printf lacks the C99 length modifiers (%hhu, %zu, %llu)
      the firmware relies on, so a small C99-capable printf from
      lib/c/newlib is linked ahead of it.

config LIBC_PICOLIBC
    bool "Picolibc"
    help
      Picolibc: smallest footprint, C99-capable printf, TLS-based
      reentrancy. Taken pre-built from the toolchain when available (the
      PebbleOS SDK toolchain ships one), otherwise built from the
      third_party/picolibc submodule with a warning.

endchoice

config LIBC_PICOLIBC_FROM_SOURCE
    bool "Build Picolibc from source"
    depends on LIBC_PICOLIBC
    help
      Always build Picolibc from the third_party/picolibc submodule with
      meson, skipping any pre-built copy the toolchain ships. Useful when
      hacking on picolibc itself or changing its build options.

endmenu
